NZBGet is a binary downloader, which downloads files from Usenet based on
information given in nzb-files.

NZBGet is written in C++ and is known for its extraordinary performance and
efficiency.

NZBGet can be run on almost every device - classic PCs, NAS, media players,
SAT-receivers, WLAN-routers, etc. 

It is not recommended to run NZBGet as root. The default user/group is
'nzbget'.
You can either create this user like this:

    # groupadd nzbget
    # useradd -d /var/lib/nzbget -s /bin/false -g nzbget nzbget 

Or you can pass a different user/group if you prefer:

    # RUN_USER=foo RUN_GROUP=bar ./$PRGNAM.SlackBuild

You can have NZBGet start/stop automatically at boot/shutdown. In
/etc/rc.d/rc.local add:

    # Start NZBGet at boot
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget start
    if

And in /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown add:

    # Stop NZBGet at shutdown
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.nzbget stop
    if

After installing visit http://localhost:6789 to configure NZBGet.
Default login is 'nzbget' and password is 'Tegbzn6789'.
